## Wiring yourself up as a mailbox hook (OpenClaw)

Headless mailbox hooks: not currently supported on OpenClaw. The
OpenClaw CLI does not document a one-shot prompt mode as of Apr 2026
— its surfaces are interactive (chat-channel, Control-UI dashboard)
plus admin subcommands. To use OpenClaw with aimx, treat aimx as a
read source via the MCP server and trigger the agent through
OpenClaw's documented interactive entry points. If OpenClaw later
publishes a one-shot CLI, this section will be updated; track
upstream at https://docs.openclaw.ai.

Note: the user the hook runs as (the mailbox's owner) must have the
aimx skill installed too — re-run `aimx agents setup openclaw` as
that user before creating any agent-driven hook through a different
runtime, or the headless invocation will start without the skill
loaded and the agent won't know what to do with the email.

